<div id="review_3542891643" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3542891643" />
    <a title="Nelly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13710666-nelly"><img alt="Nelly" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1643710722p2/13710666.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3542891643?book_show_action=true">Sep 11, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nelly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nelly" href="/user/show/13710666-nelly">Nelly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3542891643" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12545379963205740956">This was an easy read. Max Lucado&apos;s writing style is easy and friendly. I esp enjoyed the stories he uses to illustrate his points, some were really funny and I found myself chuckling.<br/><br/>Its not an in depth study of Grace or the Book of Romans but he does a decent job of speaking of salvation as something that is a gift and not something we work for.<br/><br/>He briefly touches on grace in relationships with others and that really opened my eyes to how we are called to really love like Jesus; by extending HI</span>
  <span id="freeText12545379963205740956" style="display:none">This was an easy read. Max Lucado's writing style is easy and friendly. I esp enjoyed the stories he uses to illustrate his points, some were really funny and I found myself chuckling.<br /><br />Its not an in depth study of Grace or the Book of Romans but he does a decent job of speaking of salvation as something that is a gift and not something we work for.<br /><br />He briefly touches on grace in relationships with others and that really opened my eyes to how we are called to really love like Jesus; by extending HIS GRACE to others.<br /><br />I'll definitely read this again, soon.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12545379963205740956" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


