<span id="freeTextContainer14517652141895820422">Grace, what can we say about grace? It&apos;s God&apos;s gift to us through the suffering of Jesus Christ. What can I say about grace? Every day, I thank God for his gift. This writing is a short, simple reminder of who we are to God. We can never measure up to God&apos;s standard; that is why Jesus was born, why he lived, and why he died and rose. Pastor Lucado&apos;s words are simple, based on scriptures, and well thought. Though written in 1996, the words are as true and applicable today as they were then. Every</span>
  <span id="freeText14517652141895820422" style="display:none">Grace, what can we say about grace? It's God's gift to us through the suffering of Jesus Christ. What can I say about grace? Every day, I thank God for his gift. This writing is a short, simple reminder of who we are to God. We can never measure up to God's standard; that is why Jesus was born, why he lived, and why he died and rose. Pastor Lucado's words are simple, based on scriptures, and well thought. Though written in 1996, the words are as true and applicable today as they were then. Every time I read this, I garner a little tidbit worthy of pondering. I still enjoy his illustrations about his own foibles, but my favorite will always be about driving down an alley. Grace is the blessing that we all enjoy because Christ died for all, and not just me. I am, however, happy that he died for me. </span>
