  <span id="freeText8076647100128567398" style="display:none">“Our debt is far greater than our power to repay” (153).<br />This book is a close analysis of the first part of Romans and dives deeply into the reality of grace. Each chapter is thought-provoking, and there were times when I had to put the book down or reread a paragraph because the words and the truth in them were so powerful.<br />Like the River parable at the beginning, I find myself being all of the brothers at different times, but the youngest brother is who we should strive to be. Once we have accepted grace, the decision has been made. Our names are in the Book of Life, but we must re-choose everyday how we are going to respond to that grace. “The more we immerse ourselves in grace, the more likely we are to give grace.”</span>
