        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2536608731" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9041077800245880661">Pretty good analogies and comparisons of stories that explained the love of God from a very human standpoint. I was hoping for a quick read that would be encouraging and affirming. I believe this book delivered that in many regards. There was quite a bit of humor in his delivery, which was a pleasant surprise. It was easy to read, didn&apos;t stray from the topic of grace and made the case for how God&apos;s forgiveness is a lot stronger than anything we could do wrong.<br/><br/>Of note, the story of his car insura</span>
  <span id="freeText9041077800245880661" style="display:none">Pretty good analogies and comparisons of stories that explained the love of God from a very human standpoint. I was hoping for a quick read that would be encouraging and affirming. I believe this book delivered that in many regards. There was quite a bit of humor in his delivery, which was a pleasant surprise. It was easy to read, didn't stray from the topic of grace and made the case for how God's forgiveness is a lot stronger than anything we could do wrong.<br /><br />Of note, the story of his car insurance company "letting him go" because of his family's horrible driving habits was probably one of the funniest, most relatable examples in the book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9041077800245880661" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
